## Frequently Asked Questions

### Is emotional detachment the same as depression?

No, they are not the same, but they can be related. Emotional detachment is often a symptom of depression, but you can experience it without being depressed. The complexity of mental health means symptoms often overlap. A professional diagnosis is essential to understand your specific situation and get the right support.

### Can I ever "feel" again after being numb for years?

Yes, absolutely. Feeling numb is often a protective response, and recovery is possible. Therapy can help you safely explore the reasons for the numbness and develop coping mechanisms to gradually reconnect with your emotions. Building resilience with professional guidance is key to rediscovering your capacity to feel again.

